data.chText: 桌面（显示使用程序图标的计算机屏幕）
data.enText: a screen on a computer which shows the icons of the programs that can be used

means: 桌面(显示使用程序图标的计算机屏幕)

tr: (computer science) the area of the screen in graphical user interfaces against which icons and windows appear

value.def: Desktop computers are a convenient size for using on a desk or table, but are not designed to be portable.

example.ex: When launched, the Macintosh was the smallest desktop computer ever produced.
example.tran: 当初上市的时候，麦金塔电脑是所有台式电脑里最小的。

value.def: The desktop of a computer is the display of icons that you see on the screen when the computer is ready to use.

trans: 桌面出版，桌上排版(用微型电脑和打印机进行出版业务)
